                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City policeman No.</hi> 274.) About five o'clock in the afternoon, on the 29th of July, I was in King-street, Cheapside—I saw the prisoner draw this handkerchief from a gentleman's pocket—I laid hold of him—he threw the handkerchief on the ground and struggled—I took it up, and took him to the station—I asked if he had got anything else—he said "Yes, a pocket-book"—I took it, and found the prosecutor's address in it—this is it.</p>
